this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed june 2007 mean reciprocal rank is a statistic measure for evaluating any process that produces a list of possible responses to a query ordered by probability of correctness the reciprocal rank of a query response is the multiplicative inverse of the rank of the first correct answer the mean reciprocal rank is the average of the reciprocal ranks of results for a sample of queries q 1 the reciprocal value of the mean reciprocal rank corresponds to the harmonic mean of the ranks edit example for example suppose we have the following three sample queries for a system that tries to translate english words to their plurals in each case the system makes three guesses with the first one being the one it thinks is most likely correct query results correct response rank reciprocal rank cat catten cati cats cats 3 1 3 torus torii tori toruses tori 2 1 2 virus viruses virii viri viruses 1 1 given those three samples we could calculate the mean reciprocal rank as 1 3 160 160 1 2 160 160 1 3 11 18 or about 0 61 this basic definition does not specify what to do if none of the proposed results are correct use mean reciprocal rank 0 or if there are multiple correct answers in the list consider using mean average precision map see also information retrieval and question answering 2 edit references e m voorhees 1999 proceedings of the 8th text retrieval conference trec 8 question answering track report pp 160 77 82 d r radev h qi h wu w fan 2002 evaluating web based question answering systems proceedings of lrec 